  <Name>Unmatched Authority</Name>
  <Description>Few realize the true strain of command. Balancing
the lives of oneâ€™s troops against the necessity of victory
is an impossible choice, but the best commanders
know that even greater stakes rest on their ability
to make hard decisions quickly. They must make
complex and difficult decisions and coordinate
them on the battlefield efficiently and accurately.
This requires the soldiers following their orders to
trust in their commander with the utmost faith.
Once a commander can guarantee that his troops
respect his absolute authority on the field of battle,
he has become a truly dangerous foe. Able to weave
complex maneuvers and counter-operations with
unquestioned authority, truly great commanders
all but erase the fog of war and confusion that can
bring about the downfall of even the most formidable
military force.</Description>
